## What This Module Does

This module implements the `AdvancedOutput` system for VJLive3. It allows users to take the final rendered texture and slice it, route it to different physical displays, and apply 2D perspective warping (corner pinning) or mesh warping (bezier/grid) to correct for projector angles and screen shapes. 

---

## What It Does NOT Do

- It does NOT implement complex 3D projection mapping or automatic camera-based calibration (that is a separate advanced task, P2-X4).
- It does NOT render the core VJ effects (it operates strictly on the final composed framebuffers).

